name: Fried Zucchini Sticks
author: Emo G.
summary: Our garden always produces a ton of zucchini in the summer. This is one of our favorite ways to cook it. Serve with ranch dressing for dipping.
directions: Heat oil in a deep-fryer or large saucepan to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Whisk buttermilk and eggs together in a shallow dish
Mix flour, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, baking powder, and salt together in a separate shallow dish
Dip zucchini sticks into the egg mixture; roll in bread crumbs to coat
Dip in the egg mixture again; reroll in bread crumbs
Cook breaded zucchini sticks in batches in the hot oil until golden brown, about 3 minutes per batch
Drain on a large plate lined with paper towels
